  "abstract": "The Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System (Board) is adopting a proposal to extend for three years, without revision, the Reporting, Recordkeeping, and Disclosure Requirements Associated with Regulation BB (FR BB; OMB No. 7100-0197).",
  "action": "On December 11, 2020, the Board published an initial notice in the Federal Register (85 FR 80097) requesting public comment for 60 days on the extension, without revision, of the FR BB. The comment period for this notice expired on February 9, 2021. The Board did not receive any comments. The Board adopted the extension, without revision, of the FR BB as originally proposed.",
